      <section id="id1167556599937">
        <title>To use the simple present tense to communicate [6.2.1]</title>
        <section id="id1167555772103">
          <title>WRITING IN THE SIMPLE PRESENT TENSE</title>
          <para id="id1167553211388">First choose a picture. Then choose a word that matches your picture from the list below. Decide in which room you will do what your word says. Choose one of these rooms: <emphasis effect="bold">kitchen</emphasis>, <emphasis effect="bold">lounge</emphasis>, <emphasis effect="bold">bedroom</emphasis>, <emphasis effect="bold">bathroom</emphasis>. Then write your sentence</para>
          <para id="id1167545236986"><emphasis effect="italics">For example</emphasis>: I play table tennis in the playroom.</para>
          <para id="id1167551955968">REMEMBER: </para>
          <para id="id8219046">If it is one person ( but not ‘I’ or ‘you’) that is doing something you must add -<emphasis effect="bold">s</emphasis> or -<emphasis effect="bold">es</emphasis> to the word that you choose!</para>
          <para id="id1167557519178">I       He    </para>
          <figure id="id1167553938335">
            <media id="id1167553938335_media" alt="">
              <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics3-238a.png" id="id1167553938335__onlineimage" height="188" width="500"/>
            </media>
          </figure>
          <para id="id1167553484411">She</para>
          <para id="id1167559939817">They.........</para>
          <para id="id1167557325511">We</para>
          <para id="id4689951">She</para>
          <para id="id1167559964427">We He They I</para>
          <para id="id1167549876753">SOME MORE HELP</para>
          <para id="id6964370">lunch; letters; book; teeth; music; tea; clothes; table tennis; dishes; television</para>
